definition: name/noun (part of speech)/place (e.g. among winners)/famous/classifier for people

sentences.english: A $100 registration fee per team is required.
sentences.chinese: 每队必须交100美元的报名费。

sentences.english: The refund hereby refers to the tuition, not including the registration fee.
sentences.chinese: 此处所指退费仅限学费，报名费恕不退还。

sentences.english: Entry fee is non-refundable and non- transferable once the entry is accepted.
sentences.chinese: 报名一经接纳，报名费将不获发还及不得转让。

sentences.english: Entry Fee is non-refundable and non-transferable, once the appication is accepted.
sentences.chinese: 报名一经接纳，报名费将不获发还及不得转让。

sentences.english: A $30 liability insurance fee will be collected as part of your entry fee.
sentences.chinese: 在报名费中会收取30美金的义务性保险。

sentences.english: Have her wire the registration money to me by Monday.
sentences.chinese: 你让她在星期一之前把报名费汇过来吧。

sentences.english: Registration Fee will include lunch and transportation in Shenzhen.
sentences.chinese: 报名费将会包括深圳市内舟車费及午餐。

sentences.english: Purses come from sponsorships, from entry fees and other sources.
sentences.chinese: 比赛奖金来自赞助，报名费和其他渠道。

sentences.english: Returning candidates pay only the registration fee for each exam taken.
sentences.chinese: 重考生只需要交纳每次考试的报名费。

sentences.english: Alighting Award belongs to the public welfare activities, no need to pay the entry fee.
sentences.chinese: “阿拉丁神灯奖”纯属公益活动，无需缴纳报名费。

sentences.english: The application fee is nonrefundable. Application documents will not be returned.
sentences.chinese: 如未被录取，所寄材料及报名费不予退还。

sentences.english: The fees include the postage and will not be refunded.
sentences.chinese: 考试费一律不退，报名费中包括邮费。

sentences.english: I understand and agree that the Entry Fee is non-refundable.
sentences.chinese: 本人明白一经报名，报名费将不获发还。

sentences.english: The certified athletes of Chinese Athletics Association are exempted from the registration expense.
sentences.chinese: 在中国田协注册运动员免收报名费。

sentences.english: All fees are non-refundable and non-transferable once the entry is accepted.
sentences.chinese: 报名一经接受，报名费恕不退还或转让。

sentences.english: If the race is cancelled, no entry fee will be refunded.
sentences.chinese: 如赛事取消，报名费将不予以退回。

definition: to sign up/to enter one's name/to apply/to register/to enroll/to enlist
to pay up/to shell out/to hand over the money to cover sth
to sit for a makeup exam/to resit an exam/makeup exam/resit
